WEBVTT

00:01.566 --> 00:03.046
- Previously on
"Superman and Lois"...

00:03.090 --> 00:05.222
I have stage three
inflammatory breast cancer.

00:05.266 --> 00:06.963
- Where are you going?
- "The Gazette."

00:07.007 --> 00:08.530
I'm not just gonna sit around
and wait till chemo, Clark.

00:08.573 --> 00:10.227
- There's one prisoner
other than Henry Miller

00:10.271 --> 00:12.621
that Judge Regan granted
compassionate release to.

00:12.664 --> 00:14.362
James Distefano.

00:14.405 --> 00:16.059
- You skipped chemo, Lois.

00:16.103 --> 00:18.061
- We had just gotten this break
in the Mannheim case.

00:18.105 --> 00:19.932
Bruno Mannheim
is my white whale.

00:19.976 --> 00:21.804
- This story is not more
important than your health.

00:21.847 --> 00:23.153
- Mom?
[sustained tone]

00:23.197 --> 00:25.982
- Bruno Mannheim
invested $200 million

00:26.026 --> 00:27.288
in Hob's Bay Medical Center.

00:27.331 --> 00:28.637
If a sign up
as a chemo patient there,

00:28.680 --> 00:30.465
I would be right
in the middle of Hob's Bay.

00:30.508 --> 00:32.075
I'll do the paperwork
when we get home.

00:32.119 --> 00:33.729
It'll be in their system
at the end of the day.

00:33.772 --> 00:36.427
[dramatic music]

00:37.254 --> 00:39.430
♪ ♪

00:39.474 --> 00:41.084
I think that's everything.

00:41.128 --> 00:43.739
Your dad and I will meet you at
the dance after my treatment.

00:43.782 --> 00:45.567
- Mom, you really
don't need to come, okay?

00:45.610 --> 00:47.047
Grandpa said
he'd cover for you.

00:47.090 --> 00:48.570
There's gonna be
plenty of chaperones.

00:48.613 --> 00:50.093
- But it's
the Valentine's Day Dance.

00:50.137 --> 00:51.268
I wanna be there.
- You're getting a round

00:51.312 --> 00:53.662
of chemo.
Maybe take a rest after.

00:53.705 --> 00:56.099
- Yeah, last time, you were
super exhausted, remember?

00:56.143 --> 00:59.015
- I was a little fatigued,
but not until the next day.

00:59.059 --> 01:01.931
Besides, this is my one chance
to see you two dressed in

01:01.974 --> 01:04.019
anything other than
hoodies and tennis shoes.

01:04.063 --> 01:05.804
So if you really
wanna make me happy,

01:05.848 --> 01:07.415
you'll put on a suit,
and I don't know,

01:07.458 --> 01:08.981
maybe comb your hair.
- Okay.

01:09.025 --> 01:11.506
I would, but Candice
never lets me in the bathroom.

01:11.549 --> 01:13.116
- Jordan,
we have talked about this.

01:13.160 --> 01:14.639
She's our guest.
- No, seriously, though.

01:14.683 --> 01:16.163
It's been three weeks
of cold showers,

01:16.206 --> 01:17.599
not to mention
waiting for the bathroom.

01:17.642 --> 01:19.079
- Okay, she's looking
for a place to stay.

01:19.122 --> 01:20.602
It's just taking
longer than expected.

01:20.645 --> 01:22.517
- I'm starting to think
she's my mortal enemy.

01:22.560 --> 01:24.519
- Okay.
- Oh, good, you're still here.

01:24.562 --> 01:26.738
I thought you would like
a little treat

01:26.782 --> 01:28.218
during your session today.

01:28.262 --> 01:31.178
- Aw, that is so sweet of you.

01:31.221 --> 01:32.701
- Thanks again for
taking me dress-shopping.

01:32.744 --> 01:35.138
I can't wait
to show it off at the dance.

01:35.182 --> 01:37.140
- You're gonna look
so beautiful.

01:37.184 --> 01:39.577
All right, wish me luck.

01:39.621 --> 01:40.970
Round two.

01:41.013 --> 01:43.103
- You're gonna crush it today,
Mrs. Lane.

01:43.146 --> 01:44.408
- Thank you.

01:46.410 --> 01:48.282
- Hey.

01:50.806 --> 01:52.460
- You and Nat taking them out
for another spin?

01:52.503 --> 01:54.723
- Really appreciate you
letting us use your land.

01:54.765 --> 01:56.464
- Hey, anytime.

01:56.507 --> 02:00.294
- But, Clark,
I gotta be honest,

02:00.337 --> 02:02.861
I'm not okay with Lois
getting her treatment

02:02.905 --> 02:05.516
at Bruno Mannheim's hospital.

02:05.560 --> 02:07.388
Am I the only one
who thinks the priority here

02:07.431 --> 02:09.303
should be
her beating this thing

02:09.346 --> 02:12.262
and not poking around in
Al Capone's vault?

02:12.306 --> 02:13.655
- It's Lois' treatment.

02:13.698 --> 02:15.657
She's allowed
to decide where she gets it.

02:15.700 --> 02:17.920
- Bruno Mannheim
stole your blood

02:17.963 --> 02:20.314
and then tried to blow up
John Henry's sister.

02:20.357 --> 02:22.838
Not exactly the résumé
of a top caregiver.

02:22.881 --> 02:25.362
- I'm aware of that.

02:25.406 --> 02:27.930
- At least keep her away from
the kids' dance tonight.

02:27.973 --> 02:29.845
She should be at home, resting.

02:29.888 --> 02:31.542
- She's got her heart
set on going,

02:31.586 --> 02:33.805
so we're gonna have to trust
that she knows her limits.

02:35.590 --> 02:38.201
- You still mad about me going
to Hob's Bay Medical Center?

02:38.245 --> 02:40.986
- I'm just here
to support you, pumpkin,

02:41.030 --> 02:42.510
any way I can.

02:44.207 --> 02:45.861
- Ready?

02:45.904 --> 02:47.689
- I'll see you
at the dance, Dad.

02:49.560 --> 02:52.041
- [sighs]

02:52.084 --> 02:54.522
[car door opens]

02:58.265 --> 03:01.093
[upbeat dramatic music]

03:01.137 --> 03:04.880
♪ ♪

03:04.923 --> 03:06.316
- Ms. Lane?

03:06.360 --> 03:09.406
We're all ready for you now.

03:09.450 --> 03:16.674
♪ ♪

03:46.487 --> 03:53.711
♪ ♪

04:14.297 --> 04:16.343
- It's not so bad here, huh?

04:18.127 --> 04:20.346
- Not so bad.

04:21.565 --> 04:28.268
♪ ♪

04:30.574 --> 04:32.533
[phone buzzes]
- I'm happy we're doing this.

04:32.576 --> 04:35.449
It's nice to have a meal,
you and me.

04:35.492 --> 04:37.364
- What'd you say?

04:37.407 --> 04:39.582
- I said--
- Oh, I'm sorry.

04:41.672 --> 04:44.240
- So are you excited
for the dance tonight?

04:44.284 --> 04:48.549
- No. I mean, well, not really.
It's not at school.

04:48.592 --> 04:51.073
I mean, what's
the Loyal Order of the Bison?

04:51.116 --> 04:52.553
- They were kind enough

04:52.596 --> 04:54.511
to loan us their banquet hall
for the evening.

04:54.555 --> 04:57.297
- [chuckles]
[phone buzzes]

04:57.340 --> 04:59.603
- Oh, I gotta go.

04:59.647 --> 05:01.431
Chrissy wants a statement about

05:01.475 --> 05:04.129
the town hall
construction delay.

05:04.173 --> 05:05.566
- Oof.

05:07.959 --> 05:09.570
- Hey, Junior.

05:09.613 --> 05:11.615
How are you
and your mom holding up?

05:11.659 --> 05:13.617
- Don't act like you care.

05:13.661 --> 05:15.663
- Of course I care.
- Really?

05:15.706 --> 05:17.186
'Cause now that my dad's dead,

05:17.229 --> 05:19.536
you've been acting like
he was never even the mayor.

05:19.580 --> 05:21.364
- I issued a statement.

05:21.408 --> 05:23.584
- Which was a joke.

05:23.627 --> 05:25.063
You didn't mention
any of the stuff he did

05:25.107 --> 05:26.151
for people around here.

05:26.195 --> 05:27.979
- Come on, Junior.

05:28.023 --> 05:29.764
We're all friends here.

05:29.807 --> 05:32.332
- You and I haven't been
friends for, like, ten years.

05:35.552 --> 05:37.162
I know you cheated
to beat my dad.

05:37.206 --> 05:39.817
- That is not true.

05:39.861 --> 05:41.732
- Whatever.

05:43.517 --> 05:45.082
[bell chimes]

05:45.127 --> 05:46.302
- [scoffs]

05:46.346 --> 05:49.349
[Breanna Barbara's "Rise"]

05:49.392 --> 05:57.008
♪ ♪

05:57.052 --> 05:58.358
- ♪ You ♪

05:58.401 --> 05:59.837
♪ Built a wall ♪

05:59.881 --> 06:03.493
♪ Well,
you ain't seen before ♪

06:03.537 --> 06:05.756
♪ Sire,
the sounds of reasons ♪

06:05.800 --> 06:07.889
- Last one home buys lunch!

06:07.932 --> 06:10.152
- ♪ That you have ♪

06:10.195 --> 06:11.283
♪ Whoo ♪

06:11.327 --> 06:14.286
[vocalizing]

06:14.330 --> 06:16.550
♪ ♪

06:16.593 --> 06:17.942
♪ Whoo ♪

06:17.986 --> 06:20.989
[vocalizing]

06:21.032 --> 06:24.558
♪ ♪

06:31.521 --> 06:33.480
- You are so lucky I'm vegan,

06:33.523 --> 06:35.133
or else I'd be ordering
a big, fat steak.

06:35.177 --> 06:37.308
- [chuckles]

06:37.353 --> 06:40.487
Any idea
who that is with Jordan?

06:43.272 --> 06:47.407
- Hey, Nat, guess who I found
in town looking for you?

06:50.584 --> 06:52.412
- Matteo?

06:55.545 --> 06:57.242
[chuckles]

06:57.286 --> 06:58.940
- Are you sure about this?

06:58.983 --> 07:02.160
- If I can get access
to Dr. Hook's files,

07:02.204 --> 07:04.815
maybe we can finally find out
what Bruno Mannheim's up to.

07:04.859 --> 07:08.123
- Okay, it's just the nurse
said the anti-nausea medicine

07:08.166 --> 07:10.517
might wear you out,
so maybe I should be the one

07:10.560 --> 07:11.561
doing the investigating.

07:11.605 --> 07:13.694
- Or being a patient here

07:13.737 --> 07:16.479
will allow me to move around
more freely, undetected.

07:16.523 --> 07:19.134
So you just stay here.

07:19.177 --> 07:20.657
- And do what?

07:20.701 --> 07:22.964
- Cover for me.
D

07:23.007 --> 07:24.531
uh.

07:24.574 --> 07:25.880
- [scoffs]

07:31.276 --> 07:32.843
Okay.

07:37.021 --> 07:39.328
[sinister music]

07:39.371 --> 07:42.200
- [sighs]

07:42.244 --> 07:43.898
I need more.

07:43.941 --> 07:47.118
- You do what I ask,
you'll get as much as you need.

07:47.162 --> 07:51.340
- This stuff's the only thing
that's keeping me alive.

07:51.383 --> 07:53.647
- Oh, it's doing
more than that.

07:55.039 --> 07:57.172
- Lois Lane has settled in.

07:59.130 --> 08:03.483
- Are you clear on what
you need to do, Mr. Distefano?

08:07.661 --> 08:09.619
- I'm clear.

08:09.663 --> 08:16.278
♪ ♪

08:20.891 --> 08:23.459
- Where'd she meet this joker?

08:23.503 --> 08:25.156
- Um, in Metropolis.

08:25.200 --> 08:27.550
- In Metropolis, where?

08:27.594 --> 08:28.986
- At a party.

08:29.030 --> 08:31.554
- So this Matteo shows up
in Smallville on what,

08:31.598 --> 08:32.860
a hunch?

08:32.903 --> 08:35.253
- Actually,
he found Sarah online

08:35.297 --> 08:36.690
and asked for Nat's number,

08:36.732 --> 08:38.299
but Sarah thought
it'd be better

08:38.342 --> 08:41.042
if he came to Smallville
and asked her in person, so...

08:41.085 --> 08:43.217
- Here he is,
having convinced you

08:43.260 --> 08:45.699
to ditch every safety protocol
you've been taught

08:45.742 --> 08:48.658
and lead him
straight to the farm!

08:48.702 --> 08:50.965
- He seems like a cool guy.

08:51.008 --> 08:53.315
- Cool guy?

08:53.358 --> 08:54.925
Right.

08:59.234 --> 09:00.931
- Um, I gotta be honest.

09:00.975 --> 09:03.107
That dude's
kind of freaking me out.

09:03.151 --> 09:04.413
[both chuckle]

09:04.456 --> 09:06.458
- He's probably just wondering
why you're here.

09:06.502 --> 09:08.286
- But why does he even care?

09:08.330 --> 09:12.116
- He's, you know, like,
part of my adopted family.

09:12.160 --> 09:13.204
It's complicated.

09:13.248 --> 09:15.598
- Oh, I see. I see.

09:15.642 --> 09:17.644
Well, in that case,

09:17.687 --> 09:19.907
I'll try my best
to make a good impression.

09:19.950 --> 09:21.256
- This is so crazy.

09:21.299 --> 09:23.127
I can't believe
you're actually here.

09:23.171 --> 09:24.912
- Yeah, me either.

09:24.955 --> 09:27.262
I was super nervous
surprising you like this,

09:27.305 --> 09:31.483
but Sarah insisted, so I...

09:31.527 --> 09:35.575
- Well, this time, I will
definitely give you my number.

09:35.618 --> 09:37.925
- You know,
the movie theater in town

09:37.968 --> 09:40.928
is playing "Dumb Einstein,"
if you're interested.

09:42.103 --> 09:43.278
Or maybe not.

09:43.321 --> 09:44.932
- It's just I have
a Valentine's dance

09:44.975 --> 09:46.586
that I'm going to at my school.

09:46.629 --> 09:47.978
I mean,
I'd ask you to go, but--

09:48.022 --> 09:49.284
- You already have a date.

09:49.327 --> 09:51.939
- No, it's a formal.

09:51.982 --> 09:54.594
You're not really dressed up.

09:54.637 --> 09:57.597
- Okay, well, I'll buy a suit.

09:57.640 --> 10:01.209
I'm sure there's some place
in town that could hook me up.

10:01.252 --> 10:03.864
- Seems like a lot just to go
to some high-school dance.

10:03.907 --> 10:05.822
- Not just a high school dance.

10:05.866 --> 10:07.607
A high school dance with you.

10:07.650 --> 10:08.912
- [chuckles]

10:08.956 --> 10:12.046
- It's totally worth it.

10:12.089 --> 10:14.178
- Okay.

10:15.876 --> 10:18.356
- Please have a seat.

10:18.400 --> 10:19.836
You're making me nervous.

10:19.880 --> 10:22.970
- Oh, I'm sorry.
Um, I'm not getting treatment.

10:23.013 --> 10:24.449
I'm just here
to support my wife.

10:24.493 --> 10:27.017
- Lois Lane, right?
- Mm-hmm.

10:27.061 --> 10:30.412
- Lois Lane in Hob's Bay?
- Mm. What's she got?

10:30.455 --> 10:33.633
- Uh, inflammatory
breast cancer, stage three.

10:33.676 --> 10:36.070
- This her first round
of chemo?

10:36.113 --> 10:38.986
- Second. The first one
was in New Carthage.

10:39.029 --> 10:41.945
Everything went well.
She's--she's doing great.

10:41.989 --> 10:43.773
- How are you doing?

10:45.645 --> 10:48.648
- Uh...
[chuckles]

10:48.691 --> 10:50.345
I just want Lois to get better.

10:50.388 --> 10:53.000
- Ah. Looks like
we have another one.

10:53.043 --> 10:54.479
- Sounds like
every other spouse.

10:54.523 --> 10:56.351
[both chuckling]

10:56.394 --> 10:58.179
- Have a seat.

11:02.662 --> 11:04.315
[door unlocks]

11:05.621 --> 11:08.058
- Excuse me.
Can I help you?

11:08.102 --> 11:09.973
- Yeah, I'm just
dropping off lab results.

11:10.017 --> 11:12.149
- Okay, no problem.
First door on your right.

11:12.193 --> 11:14.195
- Great.

11:17.589 --> 11:19.200
- Damn it all to hell.

11:22.377 --> 11:24.292
- Mr. Cushing.

11:27.338 --> 11:29.079
Need a hand?

11:29.123 --> 11:30.951
- I've been out here a while.
I don't know.

11:30.994 --> 11:33.954
Half a dozen cars driven by,
and you're the, uh--

11:33.997 --> 11:35.129
you're the first personto stop.

11:35.172 --> 11:36.913
- Yeah, well, it's no big deal.

11:36.957 --> 11:39.002
I just wanted to make sure
everything was okay.

11:40.700 --> 11:42.571
- See, that right there,
that's, uh,

11:42.614 --> 11:44.399
that's pretty much
what I do for a living.

11:44.442 --> 11:46.357
[sighs]

11:48.011 --> 11:50.144
You know, crew and I,
we've been, uh,

11:50.187 --> 11:53.538
we've been
pretty swamped lately.

11:53.582 --> 11:54.975
We could use an extra hand.

11:55.018 --> 11:58.021
- Wait, seriously?
- Yeah.

11:58.065 --> 12:00.502
Hell, you're the perfect age
if you want to learn,

12:00.545 --> 12:02.591
you know, if it's something
you might be interested in.

12:02.634 --> 12:05.855
- Yeah, yeah,
that would be cool.

12:05.899 --> 12:08.815
But I work during the week
at Brit and Dunn's.

12:08.858 --> 12:10.251
- Your weekends free?

12:11.469 --> 12:12.819
- Yes, sir.

12:12.862 --> 12:14.603
- Why don't you stop by
next Saturday?

12:14.646 --> 12:17.214
We'll just take it from there.

12:17.258 --> 12:18.433
- Okay.

12:18.476 --> 12:20.217
- All right. Cool.

12:20.261 --> 12:23.003
- Hey, Jon, we gotta get going
so I can get ready in time.

12:24.439 --> 12:26.093
- Go.

12:26.136 --> 12:27.616
See you next Saturday.

12:27.659 --> 12:30.793
- Will do.

12:30.837 --> 12:32.926
[trunk clicks closed]

12:32.969 --> 12:34.275
[engine turning over]

12:34.318 --> 12:36.756
- Junior was just so angry.

12:36.799 --> 12:39.454
It was like
I was the bad person,

12:39.497 --> 12:42.022
not his dad.

12:42.065 --> 12:43.893
- I'm afraid that
Junior is not the only one

12:43.937 --> 12:46.287
who feels that way.

12:46.330 --> 12:49.899
There are so many questions
about what happened to Dean.

12:49.943 --> 12:52.075
People are looking for
someone to blame.

12:52.119 --> 12:53.947
- But why blame me?

12:53.990 --> 12:56.384
I had nothing to do
with what happened.

12:56.427 --> 12:59.169
- But you were
political rivals, right?

12:59.213 --> 13:02.172
People see that
and just sort of run with it.

13:02.216 --> 13:03.783
- [scoffs]

13:03.826 --> 13:07.699
If people could only see how
crooked George Dean really was.

13:07.743 --> 13:12.052
- I mean, objectively, he did
do a lot of good for this town.

13:12.095 --> 13:16.273
- Oh, trust me, the bad
outweighs the good here.

13:16.317 --> 13:18.014
I mean, I have plenty of proof

13:18.058 --> 13:20.016
of Dean
robbing this city blind.

13:20.060 --> 13:22.149
- Lana, well,
unless people know the truth,

13:22.192 --> 13:23.977
they're gonna keep blaming you.

13:24.020 --> 13:27.981
If you want,
I can help clear the air.

13:34.161 --> 13:38.295
- Two of us, we've both
been through this before.

13:38.339 --> 13:41.298
- I was diagnosed
five years ago.

13:41.342 --> 13:44.127
Went through
all the treatments--

13:44.171 --> 13:46.521
radiation, surgery.

13:46.564 --> 13:50.568
Was in remission
until it came back.

13:50.612 --> 13:52.919
End of last year.

13:52.962 --> 13:54.964
- Sorry to hear that.

13:55.008 --> 13:58.141
- And for me, I've been on
both sides of the chair.

13:58.185 --> 14:03.843
First was where you're sitting
with my daughter Diana.

14:03.886 --> 14:05.888
She had breast cancer.

14:07.890 --> 14:11.067
Took her
three years ago this month.

14:13.156 --> 14:14.897
She would've turned 37.

14:14.941 --> 14:17.204
- Wow, she was so young.

14:17.247 --> 14:19.902
- Her doctors thought
the same thing.

14:19.946 --> 14:22.296
They kept telling her
not to worry,

14:22.339 --> 14:24.080
even though
the voice in her head

14:24.124 --> 14:26.039
knew something was wrong.

14:30.043 --> 14:33.220
- Uh, is she okay?

14:33.263 --> 14:36.527
- Oh, yeah, that's just
the chemo kicking in.

14:43.839 --> 14:46.276
- I'm really sorry
about your daughter.

14:49.105 --> 14:52.369
- Me too.
[sniffles]

14:56.156 --> 14:58.201
[door unlocks]

15:10.779 --> 15:12.912
- Where's Henry Miller?

15:15.436 --> 15:16.611
[door unlocks]

15:24.662 --> 15:27.100
- I gotta hand it to you,

15:27.143 --> 15:29.232
coming to my hospital
for treatment

15:29.276 --> 15:32.757
so you can investigate me
at the same time.

15:32.801 --> 15:34.846
- Where's Dr. Hook?

15:34.890 --> 15:38.198
- Making rounds,
seeing patients.

15:38.241 --> 15:39.808
- We both know that's not true.

15:39.851 --> 15:42.593
- Well, I can have a nurse
track him down for you,

15:42.637 --> 15:44.073
if you'd like.

15:44.117 --> 15:47.207
But all this sneaking around
is unnecessary.

15:47.250 --> 15:50.950
You wanna know something?
Just ask.

15:50.993 --> 15:55.476
- Well, what I know is that
you have Superman's blood

15:55.519 --> 15:58.870
and that you are having
Dr. Hook somehow use it

15:58.914 --> 16:00.785
to make powered people...

16:00.829 --> 16:02.135
- This again.

16:02.178 --> 16:05.181
- People who were dying
like Henry Miller.

16:05.225 --> 16:07.140
- You know,
your friend, Superman,

16:07.183 --> 16:10.143
accused me of the same thing.

16:10.186 --> 16:12.580
This is
a cancer treatment facility.

16:12.623 --> 16:15.931
The only thing I'm doing here
is trying to save lives.

16:15.975 --> 16:19.065
- I have written about you long
enough to know that nothing--

16:19.108 --> 16:21.719
nothing--
happens in South Metropolis

16:21.763 --> 16:24.331
unless it benefits you.

16:24.374 --> 16:27.160
- You want something
to write about?

16:27.203 --> 16:29.814
[dramatic music]

16:29.858 --> 16:37.083
♪ ♪

16:38.867 --> 16:42.697
This is my state-of-the-art
research lab.

16:44.915 --> 16:46.614
Follow me.

16:50.444 --> 16:54.535
[The Sugarhill Gang's
"Rapper's Delight" playing]

16:54.578 --> 16:56.232
- ♪ I said,
a hip-hop, the hippie ♪

16:56.276 --> 16:57.712
♪ The hippie
to the hip, hip-hop ♪

16:57.755 --> 16:59.148
♪ And you don't
stop the rockin' ♪

16:59.192 --> 17:00.367
♪ To the bang-bang boogie ♪

17:00.410 --> 17:02.064
♪ Say up jump the boogie ♪

17:02.108 --> 17:04.327
♪ To the rhythm of the boogie,
the beat ♪

17:04.371 --> 17:06.242
- Not sure I understand
your mother's desire

17:06.286 --> 17:07.722
to come to this thing.
- What, you didn't like

17:07.765 --> 17:09.202
going to dances
when you were in high school?

17:09.244 --> 17:11.943
- No,
I was a junior ROTC cadet.

17:11.987 --> 17:14.381
Didn't really have time
for dating or dances.

17:16.861 --> 17:18.689
- Maybe it's not too late
for you, then.

17:26.435 --> 17:29.570
- Somehow, this is exactly
what I was expecting.

17:29.613 --> 17:31.485
- Oh, my God,
you really did it.

17:31.528 --> 17:34.531
- Yeah, somehow,
he tracked me down

17:34.575 --> 17:37.404
and then drove here
and bought a suit.

17:37.447 --> 17:39.493
- Best wingwoman ever
right here.

17:39.536 --> 17:42.148
[laughter]

17:42.191 --> 17:44.759
- Come on.
We have so much to talk about.

17:48.632 --> 17:51.592
- Your wife must have
a hard time sitting still, huh?

17:51.635 --> 17:52.897
- [chuckles]

17:52.941 --> 17:55.813
- That'll change.
[chuckles]

17:55.857 --> 17:58.773
But that instinct will
come in handy down the road.

17:58.816 --> 18:01.732
- Now don't go scaring him.
- [chuckles]

18:01.776 --> 18:03.082
- Oh, no, it's okay.

18:03.125 --> 18:05.562
Uh, what do you mean?

18:05.606 --> 18:10.132
- Well, everyone calls it
something different,

18:10.176 --> 18:12.134
experiences it
in their own way,

18:12.178 --> 18:16.356
but the pull,
as I call it,

18:16.399 --> 18:19.707
happens to anyone
who sits in this chair.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.100
- The pull?

18:22.362 --> 18:24.538
- This disease,

18:24.581 --> 18:27.236
it tests every part of you,

18:27.280 --> 18:30.674
mentally, physically.

18:30.718 --> 18:34.939
And at some point,
you get this feeling,

18:34.983 --> 18:38.508
this--this pull.

18:38.552 --> 18:42.643
That it'd be so much easier
if you'd just let go.

18:42.686 --> 18:45.472
It doesn't mean that
you don't love

18:45.515 --> 18:48.127
the people in your life
or that you wanna leave 'em,

18:48.170 --> 18:50.520
but...

18:50.564 --> 18:54.742
that feeling
to give into the disease

18:54.785 --> 18:57.310
gets to be so strong.

18:57.353 --> 18:59.921
So this drive

18:59.964 --> 19:02.750
that your wife has,

19:02.793 --> 19:06.319
she's gonna need to use
all that energy to survive.

19:08.190 --> 19:11.498
- She's not wrong.

19:14.109 --> 19:15.632
- Just checking in, ladies.

19:15.676 --> 19:18.331
- All good.
- Thank you.

19:18.374 --> 19:21.508
- And where's your wife?

19:21.551 --> 19:24.902
- Hello, Smallville High.

19:26.991 --> 19:29.864
I just wanted
to give you all some good news.

19:29.907 --> 19:33.302
The mold remediation
is nearly done,

19:33.346 --> 19:36.697
which means your school
and your lives

19:36.740 --> 19:40.309
can return to normal
pretty soon.

19:45.793 --> 19:49.579
Thank you for your patience
and understanding,

19:49.623 --> 19:53.017
and please have a great night.

19:53.061 --> 19:54.758
[applause]

19:54.802 --> 19:56.543
[Stephen Sanchez & Em
Beihold's "Until I Found You"]

19:56.586 --> 19:59.110
- Uh, you two should dance.
I'll be right back.

19:59.154 --> 20:01.765
♪ ♪

20:01.809 --> 20:04.899
- Well, don't wanna
disappoint your wingwoman.

20:04.942 --> 20:06.553
- [chuckles]

20:06.596 --> 20:10.209
- ♪ Wrap me up in all your ♪

20:10.252 --> 20:12.211
- Jon.
- Hey.

20:12.254 --> 20:14.604
- I got some news.
- What's up?

20:14.648 --> 20:17.477
- Um, that was my Aunt Peggy.

20:17.520 --> 20:21.132
She called, and she said that
I can live with her...

20:21.176 --> 20:22.395
in Topeka.

20:23.787 --> 20:25.049
- Topeka?

20:25.093 --> 20:27.530
That's, like,
four hours away.

20:27.574 --> 20:30.533
- Well, we can still
see each other on weekends.

20:32.231 --> 20:33.623
- Yeah.

20:33.667 --> 20:35.712
It's a good thing
I have my truck now.

20:36.800 --> 20:38.062
- Come on.
- ♪ I said ♪

20:38.106 --> 20:40.674
♪ I would never fall ♪

20:40.717 --> 20:44.460
♪ Unless it's you
I fall into ♪

20:44.504 --> 20:46.419
♪ I was lost ♪

20:46.462 --> 20:49.900
- I'm really glad I came.

20:49.944 --> 20:51.293
- Me too.

20:51.337 --> 20:54.253
- ♪ I found you ♪

20:54.296 --> 20:55.776
- You look so beautiful.

20:55.819 --> 20:58.692
- [chuckles]
You said that already.

21:00.346 --> 21:03.262
- I just wanted to
make sure you heard me.

21:03.305 --> 21:07.570
- ♪ Until I found her ♪

21:07.614 --> 21:09.137
- Nat, I'm s--
Nat, I'm sorry.

21:09.180 --> 21:11.226
Nat!

21:11.270 --> 21:14.273
- So much for cool guy, huh?

21:14.316 --> 21:19.234
♪ ♪

21:19.278 --> 21:22.063
- I founded this center
to help my community.

21:22.106 --> 21:24.979
- Community?
- Hob's Bay.

21:25.022 --> 21:29.418
What most people
still call South Metropolis.

21:29.462 --> 21:33.379
When I was 14,
my mother fell ill.

21:34.597 --> 21:37.296
Couldn't figure out why.

21:37.339 --> 21:41.387
It turns out
our entire neighborhood

21:41.430 --> 21:45.129
was built next to
a chemical waste dump.

21:45.173 --> 21:48.263
No one even knew it was there.

21:48.307 --> 21:50.831
Tried to get the company
responsible to help, but...

21:52.702 --> 21:55.314
You think anyone gave a damn
about some cleaning lady

21:55.357 --> 21:57.533
from the Suicide Slums?

22:00.928 --> 22:02.886
After she died,

22:02.930 --> 22:07.630
I realized no one
was ever coming to save us.

22:07.674 --> 22:10.241
So I decided
right then and there

22:10.285 --> 22:12.113
I'd do it myself.

22:13.593 --> 22:16.378
Everything you see here

22:16.422 --> 22:19.033
is an extension of that belief.

22:23.820 --> 22:28.782
I will do everything
in my power to save your life.

22:28.825 --> 22:31.959
But if you try to stop me
from saving the people I love

22:32.002 --> 22:34.875
here in Hob's Bay,

22:34.918 --> 22:36.746
that's something I won't allow.

22:39.532 --> 22:41.664
[knocking at door]

22:43.927 --> 22:47.148
You should get back to
the treatment center.

22:47.191 --> 22:48.541
I'll have my people send over

22:48.584 --> 22:52.109
all of Dr. Hook's
research files.

23:02.163 --> 23:03.512
- Lois, slow down.
- I am going to scour

23:03.556 --> 23:05.253
every inch of Dr. Hook's files.

23:05.296 --> 23:08.082
Getting treatment at Hob's Bay
was exactly what we needed.

23:08.125 --> 23:09.736
Come on.
The dance already started.

23:09.779 --> 23:11.520
- Wha--
[sighs]

23:11.564 --> 23:14.175
[romantic music]

23:14.218 --> 23:19.572
♪ ♪

23:19.615 --> 23:21.400
- I never did
live that one down.

23:21.443 --> 23:23.750
- Uh, Mr. Cushing?
- Yes, sir?

23:23.793 --> 23:26.579
- So, uh, I was wondering
if maybe I could

23:26.622 --> 23:29.451
volunteer at a station
during the week instead.

23:29.495 --> 23:31.888
- I thought you worked at Brit
and Dunn's during the week?

23:31.932 --> 23:34.587
- I do, but...

23:34.630 --> 23:35.936
- But you--

23:35.979 --> 23:38.852
you want your weekends free?
- Yes.

23:38.895 --> 23:41.420
- Well, maybe this just
isn't the right fit for you.

23:41.463 --> 23:42.769
- No, it's not that.
It's just

23:42.812 --> 23:45.815
I had this other commitmentpop up.

23:45.859 --> 23:47.469
- Well, son, I guess
you're gonna have to figure out

23:47.513 --> 23:48.949
which one's
more important to you.

23:48.992 --> 23:50.690
[Shaker Neon's
"Lose Control" playing]

23:50.733 --> 23:53.867
- ♪ How it feels ♪

23:53.910 --> 23:56.957
♪ When you're near me ♪

23:57.000 --> 23:58.088
♪ ♪

23:58.132 --> 24:02.441
♪ When you come near me ♪

24:02.484 --> 24:04.138
♪ I lose control ♪

24:05.661 --> 24:07.141
- Say the word,
and I'll go in there

24:07.184 --> 24:09.448
and scare the living hell
out of that kid.

24:09.491 --> 24:12.015
- No, he didn't do
anything wrong.

24:14.104 --> 24:15.628
It's me.

24:18.500 --> 24:20.850
- You wanna talk about it?

24:22.504 --> 24:25.333
- You wouldn't understand.

24:25.376 --> 24:29.119
- Maybe not, but...

24:29.163 --> 24:30.512
I can try.

24:40.130 --> 24:42.263
- I've never...

24:42.306 --> 24:44.961
kissed anyone before.

24:45.005 --> 24:48.269
I mean, I've never even
dated anyone before.

24:48.312 --> 24:50.706
Now there's this guy inside
who really likes me,

24:50.750 --> 24:54.231
and I really like him, but...

24:54.275 --> 24:57.887
I'm just so far behind everyone
else in this kind of stuff.

25:00.760 --> 25:05.286
- Last time I had anything
resembling a relationship

25:05.329 --> 25:08.507
was the night my wife left me.

25:08.550 --> 25:10.160
That was over 30 years ago.

25:13.468 --> 25:15.557
You get to be my age,

25:15.601 --> 25:20.562
you start to feel behind
everyone in almost everything,

25:20.606 --> 25:23.086
especially
the romance department.

25:23.130 --> 25:25.045
- [chuckles]

25:26.960 --> 25:29.919
I can't go back in there.

25:29.963 --> 25:32.400
He's gonna think
I'm some kind of weirdo.

25:32.443 --> 25:34.358
- [scoffs]

25:34.402 --> 25:36.230
The way that kid's been
looking at you all day,

25:36.273 --> 25:38.275
there's nothing you can do
to make him think that.

25:43.193 --> 25:45.544
- Why am I so scared?

25:45.587 --> 25:48.938
- [chuckling]
Because love is scary.

25:50.940 --> 25:54.074
Now, you are
the toughest kid I know.

25:55.466 --> 25:57.251
You can do this.

25:58.774 --> 26:00.602
- Thanks, Grandpa.

26:04.606 --> 26:08.567
- ♪ How will I ever forget? ♪

26:08.610 --> 26:10.090
- Hey.

26:13.702 --> 26:15.922
I saw you leave
after my mom spoke,

26:15.965 --> 26:19.099
and I--I just wanted to see
if you were okay.

26:20.491 --> 26:22.798
Junior?

26:22.842 --> 26:25.801
- [crying softly]

26:25.845 --> 26:27.934
I miss him, Sarah.

26:29.805 --> 26:32.155
I miss my dad.
- Junior, come here.

26:32.199 --> 26:34.636
- [sobbing]

26:34.680 --> 26:36.856
I miss him so much.

26:39.162 --> 26:41.600
- You're gonna ignore me
on my last night in Smallville?

26:43.079 --> 26:45.952
Hey, I know
long-distance relationships

26:45.995 --> 26:47.823
don't normally work out,
but, I mean,

26:47.867 --> 26:49.433
with everything
we've been through already,

26:49.477 --> 26:50.913
I'm sure we can make it.

26:54.351 --> 26:58.791
- So, uh, that thing
that I was telling you about,

26:58.834 --> 27:01.968
the fire station...

27:02.011 --> 27:03.796
Mr. Cushing said that
he could only use me

27:03.839 --> 27:05.667
if it was on the weekends.

27:07.364 --> 27:10.585
Which means that the only way
I could see you is...

27:10.629 --> 27:13.153
- If you turn it down.

27:13.196 --> 27:15.198
- Right, which I was gonna--
- You can't do that.

27:15.242 --> 27:17.287
- No, I--I have to.
- No, you don't.

27:17.331 --> 27:18.898
- But I wanna see you.

27:18.941 --> 27:21.248
- Yeah, and I wanna see you,
but what you've done for me,

27:21.291 --> 27:22.858
what your family's done for me,I mean,

27:22.902 --> 27:25.469
you've all sacrificed so much
to help me.

27:25.513 --> 27:28.168
You're not turning this down.

27:28.211 --> 27:32.912
- So when are we gonna
see each other?

27:32.955 --> 27:35.741
- We'll figure something out.

27:38.961 --> 27:42.225
- I love you, Candice.

27:42.269 --> 27:44.837
- I love you too.

27:50.799 --> 27:54.542
[Charley Crockett's
"I Need Your Love" playing]

27:54.585 --> 27:58.024
♪ ♪

27:58.067 --> 27:59.547
- You know,
I know we went to high school

27:59.590 --> 28:01.549
at different times, but, uh,

28:01.592 --> 28:04.639
were your dances
always this boring?

28:04.683 --> 28:06.728
- Yeah, pretty much.
- [chuckles]

28:06.772 --> 28:08.687
- Hi, you guys.

28:08.730 --> 28:11.515
both: Hey.
- Have you seen Sarah?

28:11.559 --> 28:13.387
- No.
- No.

28:13.430 --> 28:15.171
No, sorry.

28:15.215 --> 28:16.956
- All right.
I'll go find her.

28:16.999 --> 28:24.224
♪ ♪

28:25.355 --> 28:27.009
- You know,
maybe I should get going.

28:28.794 --> 28:31.231
- No, no.

28:31.274 --> 28:32.885
Not yet.

28:32.928 --> 28:36.105
[sighs]
See, I think, uh--

28:36.149 --> 28:40.153
I think Cush could use your
help with a little something.

28:40.196 --> 28:43.591
- Did you just refer to
yourself by your own nickname?

28:43.634 --> 28:46.202
- I believe I did, yes.

28:46.246 --> 28:52.774
♪ ♪

28:52.818 --> 28:56.038
[indistinct chatter]

28:59.520 --> 29:03.350
- ♪ As soon as
I get my head around you ♪

29:03.393 --> 29:06.745
♪ I come around
catching sparks off you ♪

29:06.788 --> 29:10.487
♪ I get an electric charge
from you ♪

29:10.531 --> 29:13.577
♪ That secondhand living,
it just won't do ♪

29:13.621 --> 29:16.232
[The Jesus and Mary Chain's
"Head On" playing]

29:16.276 --> 29:17.625
- Whoo!

29:17.668 --> 29:20.193
♪ ♪

29:20.236 --> 29:22.630
- ♪ And the way
I feel tonight ♪

29:22.673 --> 29:24.850
- What are you doing, Chrissy?

29:24.893 --> 29:27.156
- ♪ I wouldn't mind ♪

29:27.200 --> 29:30.943
♪ And there's something
going on inside ♪

29:30.986 --> 29:32.771
♪ Makes you wanna feel ♪

29:32.814 --> 29:34.468
♪ Makes you wanna try ♪

29:34.511 --> 29:37.863
♪ Makes you wanna blow
the stars from the sky ♪

29:37.906 --> 29:39.342
♪ I can't stand up ♪

29:39.386 --> 29:41.127
♪ I can't cool down ♪

29:41.170 --> 29:46.567
♪ I can't get my head
off the ground ♪

29:46.610 --> 29:51.006
♪ ♪

29:51.050 --> 29:54.009
[dramatic music]

29:54.053 --> 29:59.058
♪ ♪

29:59.101 --> 30:00.799
- Why aren't you dressed?

30:00.842 --> 30:02.104
- Well, look, babe,
the boys said

30:02.148 --> 30:03.410
they were gonna get photos,

30:03.453 --> 30:06.892
so why don't we just
hang out here tonight?

30:06.935 --> 30:10.634
- Why are you
telling me this right now?

30:10.678 --> 30:13.594
- I'm trying to be supportive,
and I'm following your lead,

30:13.637 --> 30:16.989
but sometimes it feels like
no one's allowed to have

30:17.032 --> 30:19.078
an opinion about
your treatment other than you.

30:20.557 --> 30:22.690
- Because it's happening to me.
- Yeah, I know.

30:22.733 --> 30:24.866
I get it,
but everything I've read

30:24.910 --> 30:28.000
and everyone I've spoken to,
they all say the same thing--

30:28.043 --> 30:30.829
that this is gonna be
the fight of your life

30:30.872 --> 30:32.265
and you need to rest.

30:32.308 --> 30:35.050
- And I will,
but not tonight.

30:35.094 --> 30:36.922
I am going
to this dance, Clark.

30:36.965 --> 30:39.054
It is very,
very important to me.

30:39.098 --> 30:40.360
And if you wanna
come with me, great,

30:40.403 --> 30:42.536
but I need you to get dressed.

30:45.931 --> 30:47.715
[siren wailing]

30:47.758 --> 30:50.761
- Find out where the hell
that breach is coming from now.

30:50.805 --> 30:52.024
- Yes, ma'am.

30:52.067 --> 30:54.461
[grunting]
[neck snaps]

30:54.504 --> 30:56.506
[device beeps]
[alarm blaring]

31:01.903 --> 31:05.080
- What do you want?[grunts]

31:05.124 --> 31:08.562
- Access
to your biggest secrets.

31:13.436 --> 31:15.569
- I know you wanna go to
the dance, but...

31:15.612 --> 31:18.615
I still think
we should talk about this.

31:18.659 --> 31:20.661
- Okay. I'm listening.

31:20.704 --> 31:24.186
[alarm blaring]
- Do it now, General.

31:24.230 --> 31:26.710
- Just wait for me, please.

31:26.754 --> 31:28.974
[air booms]

31:34.675 --> 31:36.459
[alarm blaring]

31:36.503 --> 31:39.593
- You're going to give me
what I want, General.

31:46.643 --> 31:47.906
[device beeps]

31:47.949 --> 31:49.255
- [grunts]

31:49.298 --> 31:52.432
[suspenseful music]

31:52.475 --> 31:55.826
♪ ♪

31:55.870 --> 31:58.438
[zapping]

32:04.444 --> 32:05.662
- Go.

32:09.797 --> 32:14.541
♪ ♪

32:17.761 --> 32:20.590
[grunting]

32:20.634 --> 32:27.641
♪ ♪

32:45.311 --> 32:47.966
- [heavy breathing]

32:48.009 --> 32:49.663
- [groans]

32:49.706 --> 32:56.757
♪ ♪

33:06.462 --> 33:09.770
[distorted boom]

33:12.860 --> 33:16.342
- [groaning]

33:18.692 --> 33:20.911
Too late, Superman.

33:20.955 --> 33:23.784
[electronic chime]

33:23.827 --> 33:25.525
[Lynzi & Jason Cadden's
"Keep My Eyes on You" playing]

33:25.568 --> 33:27.918
- ♪ Keep my eyes on you ♪

33:27.962 --> 33:31.966
♪ ♪

33:32.010 --> 33:35.230
♪ Only you and me, baby ♪

33:35.274 --> 33:37.406
- You don't have to leave.

33:37.450 --> 33:39.887
I mean, unless you want to.
- What?

33:39.930 --> 33:43.064
No way. I--
I just thought that since--

33:43.108 --> 33:47.112
- No, I want you to stay.Please.

33:47.155 --> 33:48.548
- Oh.

33:50.506 --> 33:51.812
Good.

33:51.855 --> 33:54.641
- Can we just pick up
where we left off?

33:54.684 --> 33:57.513
Maybe before I ran outside
like an idiot?

33:59.037 --> 34:00.299
- Whatever you want.

34:00.342 --> 34:02.388
- ♪ Fighting for someone ♪

34:02.431 --> 34:05.086
♪ To look at me
the way you do ♪

34:05.130 --> 34:09.438
- I'm sorry about
what I said at the diner.

34:09.482 --> 34:11.571
The reason
we haven't been friends...

34:13.355 --> 34:15.879
That's on me.

34:15.922 --> 34:19.100
- Maybe we could start again.

34:20.406 --> 34:22.668
If you want, I mean.

34:22.712 --> 34:26.063
[both chuckle]

34:35.246 --> 34:36.770
To your dad.

34:42.123 --> 34:43.646
[coughing]
- [chuckling]

34:43.690 --> 34:46.127
- That's terrible.
- Yeah.

34:46.170 --> 34:48.737
Yeah, my dad only ever
drank the cheap stuff.

34:48.782 --> 34:52.264
[laughter]

34:54.092 --> 34:56.268
- Get inside, Junior.

35:01.360 --> 35:04.058
- Mom--
- I can't believe you.

35:04.102 --> 35:05.407
After everything
we've been through,

35:05.451 --> 35:06.930
you go
and pull something like this?

35:06.974 --> 35:08.454
- Mom,
I'm not pulling anything.

35:08.497 --> 35:10.151
- You've been out here
drinking all night.

35:10.195 --> 35:13.241
- Mom, can I--can I explain?

35:13.285 --> 35:17.463
Look, I just came out here
to check on Junior.

35:17.506 --> 35:20.640
I know he was really angry
earlier, but...

35:20.683 --> 35:22.381
it was about him
losing his dad.

35:22.424 --> 35:24.078
And I know what
Mayor Dean said

35:24.122 --> 35:27.168
about you, about me,
about our family,

35:27.212 --> 35:29.127
but none of that
really matters anymore,

35:29.170 --> 35:32.130
and he was a good dad.

35:32.173 --> 35:34.915
Now all Junior has
are memories.

35:37.570 --> 35:39.485
I was just trying to be
a good friend.

35:41.791 --> 35:44.054
- I understand.

35:44.098 --> 35:46.100
- You do?
- I do.

35:46.144 --> 35:49.669
Just next time, no drinking.

35:54.108 --> 35:56.458
Come on.
The dance is almost over.

35:56.502 --> 35:58.678
- [sighs]

36:01.028 --> 36:02.812
- Lois.

36:02.856 --> 36:04.379
- I'm in here.

36:08.644 --> 36:09.689
- You okay?

36:11.169 --> 36:13.345
- Not really.

36:15.042 --> 36:17.697
[sighs shakily]

36:19.525 --> 36:23.529
I want to go so badly,
but I can't.

36:25.313 --> 36:27.185
Honey, you were right.

36:27.228 --> 36:30.536
Just 'cause I have cancer, it
doesn't mean I can't be wrong.

36:32.799 --> 36:36.194
I'm not the only one who gets
to have an opinion in all this.

36:41.068 --> 36:45.551
I need you
to keep sharing yours with me,

36:45.594 --> 36:48.684
especially if I don't agree.

36:48.728 --> 36:50.033
You promise?

36:50.077 --> 36:52.035
- Promise.

36:52.079 --> 36:55.038
[soft somber music]

36:55.082 --> 37:00.740
♪ ♪

37:05.310 --> 37:06.659
- [laughing]
- So how was it?

37:06.702 --> 37:09.401
- It was okay, I guess.
Nothing crazy.

37:09.444 --> 37:11.838
- Please tell me
you got pictures.

37:11.881 --> 37:14.841
- Oh, I'm sorry, Mrs. Lane.
We totally forgot.

37:14.884 --> 37:16.886
- That was my once chance to
see everyone

37:16.930 --> 37:18.323
dressed up and dancing.

37:21.326 --> 37:22.979
- Maybe not.

37:25.025 --> 37:27.897
[Girls' "My Ma" playing]

37:27.941 --> 37:30.117
♪ ♪

37:30.160 --> 37:33.076
If you're up for it.

37:33.120 --> 37:35.731
- Look at you.

37:35.775 --> 37:42.782
♪ ♪

37:45.698 --> 37:48.135
- You better dance with me.

37:48.178 --> 37:51.007
- Of course.

37:51.051 --> 37:53.923
- If you're asking me to dance,
the answer's a firm no.

37:53.967 --> 37:55.751
- [chuckles]

37:55.795 --> 37:58.232
I was thinking about
what you said earlier,

37:58.276 --> 38:00.669
and I stole your phone
in the car.

38:00.713 --> 38:03.629
- "SeniorSwipe"?
Oh, I don't think so.

38:03.672 --> 38:06.371
- Okay, come on. Come on.
It's really easy to use.

38:06.414 --> 38:07.981
All you gotta do
is swipe on the screen.

38:08.024 --> 38:11.071
And if someone
catches your eye,

38:11.114 --> 38:13.334
send them a message.

38:13.378 --> 38:18.426
♪ ♪

38:18.470 --> 38:20.559
Maybe you can find
your next dance partner.

38:20.602 --> 38:22.648
- ♪ You're my life ♪

38:22.691 --> 38:25.303
♪ And you're my ma ♪

38:25.346 --> 38:32.310
♪ ♪

38:32.353 --> 38:34.921
- Mind if I cut in?

38:34.964 --> 38:36.444
- By all means.

38:36.488 --> 38:38.533
♪ ♪

38:38.577 --> 38:39.795
- Hey, cutie.

38:39.839 --> 38:43.756
♪ ♪

38:43.799 --> 38:45.497
- [sighs]

38:45.540 --> 38:47.673
- You washed your hair?
- Mom.

38:47.716 --> 38:51.459
- Okay. Okay, I'll stop.

38:54.288 --> 38:55.942
- I love you, Mom.

38:57.596 --> 38:59.293
- [mouths] I love you.

38:59.337 --> 39:00.990
- [mouths]
I love you.

39:01.034 --> 39:06.256
♪ ♪

39:06.300 --> 39:07.823
- That was great.

39:07.867 --> 39:09.216
- [chuckles]

39:09.259 --> 39:11.087
- You were great.
[chuckles]

39:11.131 --> 39:14.003
- [chuckles]

39:14.047 --> 39:17.224
Yeah, well, you're pretty great
yourself, you know that?

39:17.267 --> 39:19.966
- Yeah, you have no idea.
- Mm.

39:20.009 --> 39:21.663
[phone buzzing]
- [chuckles]

39:21.707 --> 39:24.884
- That might be Lois.

39:27.016 --> 39:29.236
Or your ex-wife.

39:29.279 --> 39:32.326
- [sighs]
What does she want?

39:32.370 --> 39:37.331
- I don't know. It just says
she needs to see me.

39:37.375 --> 39:38.550
[sighs]

39:38.593 --> 39:40.856
- [exhales]

39:42.641 --> 39:45.600
[tense music]

39:45.644 --> 39:50.953
♪ ♪

39:50.997 --> 39:52.564
- Hey.

39:56.568 --> 39:58.744
What's up?

39:58.787 --> 40:01.703
- I don't want to go public
with that stuff about Dean.

40:03.444 --> 40:05.707
- Sorry.
What changed your mind?

40:05.751 --> 40:07.405
I mean,
don't you think that the public

40:07.448 --> 40:09.407
deserves to know the truth?

40:09.450 --> 40:11.147
- I think,
in this specific case,

40:11.191 --> 40:13.498
the truth will hurt
more than it heals.

40:13.541 --> 40:15.021
It's best to keep it a secret.

40:15.064 --> 40:17.327
- But after everything
that's happened...

40:17.371 --> 40:19.808
- This town needs closure,
Chrissy,

40:19.852 --> 40:22.681
and I'm gonna give it to them.

40:22.724 --> 40:26.249
So I've decided to name
the new town hall

40:26.293 --> 40:27.294
after Mayor Dean.

40:27.337 --> 40:29.209
- Mm.

40:29.252 --> 40:32.168
The George Dean
Memorial Town Hall.

40:32.212 --> 40:34.606
- Mm-hmm.

40:34.649 --> 40:36.477
- Sounds nice.

40:40.612 --> 40:43.136
- That everything?
- That's everything.

40:43.179 --> 40:45.530
- If you need anything at all,
you know where to find me.

40:45.573 --> 40:47.532
- Thanks, Mrs. Lane.

40:52.885 --> 40:54.452
You're just the sweetest.

40:54.495 --> 40:56.279
Take care of your brother
for me.

40:56.323 --> 40:57.846
- Okay.

41:02.590 --> 41:05.071
- Drive safe, you two.

41:05.114 --> 41:06.638
[engine turning over]

41:07.682 --> 41:11.381
- [exhales sharply]

41:11.425 --> 41:13.732
We need to talk.

41:13.775 --> 41:15.516
Turns out
this Deadline character

41:15.560 --> 41:19.651
managed to get the locations of
several of our top facilities.

41:19.694 --> 41:21.348
- What kind of facilities?

41:21.391 --> 41:23.481
- Ones that store
sensitive assets.

41:23.524 --> 41:25.178
So while you were
fighting Deadline,

41:25.221 --> 41:28.747
the rest of Intergang was
silently raiding the cupboards.

41:28.790 --> 41:30.183
- What did they take?

41:30.226 --> 41:33.403
[dramatic music]

41:33.447 --> 41:35.144
- This is our new priority.

41:35.188 --> 41:36.929
- Looks just like him,

41:36.972 --> 41:38.147
only more dead.

41:38.191 --> 41:39.409
- For now.

41:39.453 --> 41:46.678
♪ ♪

41:55.556 --> 41:58.516
[dramatic music]

41:58.559 --> 42:05.784
♪ ♪
